- `p.innerOffsetPart v` is `p.innerOffsetPart` applied to `v`. `p.innerOffsetPart` is likely a function that adds the offset to the input vector. So, `p.innerOffsetPart v = v + p.innerOffset`.

The left side `proj_xy v + p.innerOffset` can be seen as adding the projection of `v` onto the xy-plane with the offset vector. The right side `proj_xy (p.innerOffsetPart v)` applies the projection to the result of `p.innerOffsetPart v`.

