Now we can combine `h3` and `h4` to complete the proof:

```tactics
rw [h3] at h1
rw [h4] at h1
exact h1
```

So we have shown `p.shift '' closure (innerShadow p.zeroOffset S) = closure (innerShadow p S)`, which is the desired result.

The key insight is that `p.zeroOffset = p.inner`, so `innerShadow p.zeroOffset S = innerShadow p S`. Therefore, applying `p.shift` to the closure of `innerShadow p.zeroOffset S` is the same as applying `p.shift` to the closure of `innerShadow p S`. Since `p.shift` is an homeomorphism, it preserves the equality.
